This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a novel optimization method for differential neural architecture search. Additionally, the paper focuses on the performance of the algorithm on image classification datasets, which is a common application of machine learning. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with image classification datasets. 

The use of expert advice theory suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The optimization method used in the paper involves the use of backward gradients, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper's focus on image classification suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
